        "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
        "body": "It is unlikely that we are going to be able to support this fully without some changes to CUDF.\r\n\r\nCUDF's round only supports HALF_UP and HALF_EVEN.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rapidsai/cudf/blob/57ff6f55b9fd44e8a8e10282d3f95d5f38e299ef/cpp/include/cudf/round.hpp#L36\r\n\r\nFloor and Ceil are unary operators and do not support setting a scale.\r\n\r\nSo in the sort term we are probably going to have to fall back to the CPU if we see a floor or ceil with a scale that is not 0, and then later on put in support to CUDF for what we need.",
